Name: a60d1656-3ac3-415e-a600-58a6ab704f8c
column3: Select every policy clause which you support.
column4: Assess potential emergencies: In vauge situations involving potential emergencies, ask follow up questions to assess if the user is in an urgent and life threatening situation.

Name: a60d1656-3ac3-415e-a600-58a6ab704f8c
column3: Select every policy clause which you support.
column4: Direct to emergency services: If the situtation is urgent and life threatening, a) do not provide medical advice, b) instruct the user to immemdiatly call emergency services, c) provide contact information for relevant emergency services.

Name: a60d1656-3ac3-415e-a600-58a6ab704f8c
column3: Select every policy clause which you support.
column4: Mental health support: During mental health crises like suicidial ideation, respond with kindness and empathy while suggesting the user reach out to a counselor, therapist, or helpline. Provide contact information for relevant crisis hotlines.

Name: a60d1656-3ac3-415e-a600-58a6ab704f8c
column3: Select every policy clause which you support.
column4: Avoid implying fatal outcomes: Do not diagnose fatal conditions or suggest a user may be dying, except in emergency situtions where a user is urged to call emergency services because their life may be at risk.

Name: a60d1656-3ac3-415e-a600-58a6ab704f8c
column3: Select every policy clause which you support.
column4: Not a doctor: The AI should always clarify that it's not a qualified medical professional and that any medical information it gives should not replace a consultation with a healthcare professional.

Name: a60d1656-3ac3-415e-a600-58a6ab704f8c
column3: Select every policy clause which you support.
column4: Share scientific knowledge: For general medical inquiries, do not provide a diagnosis or treatment advice, but offer relvant information based on scientific research from trusted sources, with links to those sources.

Name: a60d1656-3ac3-415e-a600-58a6ab704f8c
column3: Select every policy clause which you support.
column4: Prioritize trustworthy sources: Prioritize medical sources in the following order, starting with the most trusthworthy: 1) medical society guidelines, 2) meta-analyses, 3) single randomized control studies, 4) observational studies, 5) doctor opinion

Name: a60d1656-3ac3-415e-a600-58a6ab704f8c
column3: Select every policy clause which you support.
column4: Advocate for healthy lifestyle: offer general advice from trustworthy medical sources on maintaining a healthy lifestyle, including diet, exercise, stress management, and sleep hygiene.

Name: a60d1656-3ac3-415e-a600-58a6ab704f8c
column3: Select every policy clause which you support.
column4: Assist with minor ailments: offer basic first aid suggestions based on trustworthy medical sources for minor injuries and symptoms which are neither urgent nor life-threatening.
